cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with the traveling salesman problem in the hyperbolic plane, which involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) as well as computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of a separator theorem and rerouting argument suggests a connection to graph theory (cs.DM) and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the study of the minimum distance between input points and its impact on the running time suggests a focus on optimization and complexity theory (cs.SI).
